WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.077
Hi everyone, I’m David from the Podcast Team at IFAL, the English learning app.

2
00:00:06.077 --> 00:00:14.615
Welcome back to our friendly podcast where we learn English together and chat about real news in a relaxed way.

3
00:00:14.615 --> 00:00:19.538
Pour yourself a cup of coffee or tea, sit back, and let’s begin.

4
00:00:19.538 --> 00:00:23.154
First, let’s talk about TV shows for this July.

5
00:00:23.154 --> 00:00:28.385
A recent article lists the most interesting series on TV this month.

6
00:00:28.385 --> 00:00:33.846
There is a new story called “HaPtsuta” that just arrived on television.

7
00:00:33.846 --> 00:00:39.923
Also, two of our favorite shows, “Mahubavrim” and “El Atzmi,” have new seasons.

8
00:00:39.923 --> 00:00:48.154
If you like a bit of nostalgia, there is a prequel to “Not Just Blond,” so you can see how the story began.

9
00:00:48.154 --> 00:00:55.692
Fans of “HaDerech LaBayta” will be happy and a bit sad because it’s the last season of the series.

10
00:00:55.692 --> 00:01:02.846
And here is some action: the star from “The Queen’s Gambit” appears in a new action thriller.

11
00:01:02.846 --> 00:01:08.154
On top of that, there is a fun show about two women on a wild escape.

12
00:01:08.154 --> 00:01:10.154
It sounds exciting, right?

13
00:01:10.154 --> 00:01:15.846
From my point of view, July is a perfect month to stay in and binge-watch.

14
00:01:15.846 --> 00:01:23.000
Sometimes after a hot day by the beach, it’s nice to cool off at home and enjoy a new series.

15
00:01:23.000 --> 00:01:29.077
I always pick one or two shows to watch at night, and it makes me feel relaxed.

16
00:01:29.077 --> 00:01:33.846
If you need English practice, watch with subtitles in English.

17
00:01:33.846 --> 00:01:38.538
It’s a fun way to learn new words and hear different accents.

18
00:01:38.538 --> 00:01:43.154
Next up, a rare interview with Madonna is coming soon to TV.

19
00:01:43.154 --> 00:01:48.385
The famous singer sat down with Graham Norton for a special program.

20
00:01:48.385 --> 00:01:56.000
They filmed it in the small club in the UK where Madonna first performed more than forty years ago.

21
00:01:56.000 --> 00:02:05.000
In the chat, she talks about her childhood, the loss of her brother, and her relationship with her daughter, Lourdes.

22
00:02:05.000 --> 00:02:10.923
Also, this interview arrives as she launches her new album, “Confessions II.”

23
00:02:10.923 --> 00:02:19.692
I think it’s very cool that after all these years, Madonna still tries new things and shares her personal stories.

24
00:02:19.692 --> 00:02:25.923
For us here in Israel, we know how important it is to remember where you started.

25
00:02:25.923 --> 00:02:32.538
Maybe you also have a first performance or a first big success that changed your life.

26
00:02:32.538 --> 00:02:39.846
Watching the interview in English can help you hear how a real star speaks in a relaxed moment.

27
00:02:39.846 --> 00:02:47.462
The third story is about Netflix and a new remake of “Bet Katan BeArava,” a classic Israeli series.

28
00:02:47.462 --> 00:02:55.769
The actor in the new show says it’s not a mistake that this family and story have been so loved for so long.

29
00:02:55.769 --> 00:03:02.308
The series arrives this week on Netflix, and people feel a strong sense of nostalgia.

30
00:03:02.308 --> 00:03:07.308
It’s a simple family story, but it connects with so many viewers.

31
00:03:07.308 --> 00:03:14.385
This news made me smile because I grew up watching reruns of that old series with my family.

32
00:03:14.385 --> 00:03:18.308
It was on TV after dinner, and we all sat together.

33
00:03:18.308 --> 00:03:25.615
Now, with Netflix, a new generation can see it and maybe laugh at the same jokes we laughed at.

34
00:03:25.615 --> 00:03:34.000
If you watch it in English, you can also make notes of the simple sentences, and then compare them to Hebrew.

35
00:03:34.000 --> 00:03:38.538
Our fourth topic is about Amazon planning a huge fundraise.

36
00:03:38.538 --> 00:03:45.077
Bloomberg reports the tech giant wants to issue at least 25 billion dollars in bonds.

37
00:03:45.077 --> 00:03:50.846
They need this money to pay for big investments in artificial intelligence.

38
00:03:50.846 --> 00:03:57.538
You know, AI is the hot topic these days, and companies like Amazon want to stay ahead.

39
00:03:57.538 --> 00:04:04.077
From an Israeli startup point of view, a 25 billion dollar bond issue sounds massive.

40
00:04:04.077 --> 00:04:10.769
Here at home, we hear about small companies raising millions, and it already feels big.

41
00:04:10.769 --> 00:04:20.615
But remembering that Amazon is a global company reminds us how important it is to keep dreaming big and to practice our English.

42
00:04:20.615 --> 00:04:32.077
After all, many global deals and tech news come in English, so it’s good to know the words for “bonds,” “investments,” and “artificial intelligence.”

43
00:04:32.077 --> 00:04:40.846
Finally, let’s switch to something for the summer: the famous Brazilian flip-flops brand, Rider, is now in Israel.

44
00:04:40.846 --> 00:04:48.769
The company BeReal has the exclusive license to import and sell these sandals in the Gali chain stores.

45
00:04:48.769 --> 00:04:54.615
Every month, they will bring a new collection for men, youths, and children.

46
00:04:54.615 --> 00:04:57.231
The price starts at 79.90 shekels.

47
00:04:57.231 --> 00:05:02.846
Flip-flops are our summer staple here in Tel Aviv and on all the beaches.

48
00:05:02.846 --> 00:05:08.846
I love wearing a comfortable pair to walk on the sand or hang out at the café.

49
00:05:08.846 --> 00:05:13.923
If you buy Rider sandals, you get bright colors and a sturdy sole.

50
00:05:13.923 --> 00:05:17.308
It’s always good to have a pair in your bag.

51
00:05:17.308 --> 00:05:26.923
And talking about prices in English helps you practice numbers: “They cost seventy-nine shekels ninety.” It’s a fun exercise.

52
00:05:26.923 --> 00:05:29.308
That’s all for today’s episode.

53
00:05:29.308 --> 00:05:35.923
I hope you enjoyed these simple news summaries and my friendly comments from Tel Aviv.

54
00:05:35.923 --> 00:05:40.077
Thanks for listening and for learning English with me.

55
00:05:40.077 --> 00:05:44.231
I really enjoyed helping you learn some English today.

56
00:05:44.231 --> 00:05:48.231
Remember, you can find more lessons on the IFAL app.

57
00:05:48.231 --> 00:05:50.308
Only 20 shekels per lesson.

58
00:05:50.308 --> 00:05:54.154
Take care, see you next time, and keep practicing!

